    {
        "id": "(專)法學院高階主管法律碩士在職專班",
        "name": "ESG與法律專題研究(二)",
        "professor": "廖宗聖",
        "credits": 2,
        "time": "六9,10",
        "location": "台北校區教室1",
        "type": "選修",
        "description": "1. 「永續發展」概念、定義及議題係從國際環境法發展而來，2015年至2030年聯合國制訂永續發展目標（SDGs），做為各國遵循的目標指引。另一方面，2005年聯合國倡議：「金融機構負責任的投資」，進而提出ESG（環境、社會及治理）投資的指標，並作為引導的依據。處於永續發展及永續金融的趨勢下，對我國公、私部門（特別是企業）而言，不僅是挑戰也是機會。\r\n2.ESG與法律（一）的課程重點在於氣候變遷、淨零排放與法律的部分，ESG與法律（二）的部分將會重心放在整體ESG與法律部分。\r\n3.時間：每位老師上課一次，每次4個小時。\r\n1. The concept, definition, and issues surrounding \"Sustainable Development\" originated from the development of international environmental law. From 2015 to 2030, the United Nations established the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) to serve as a guiding framework for nations to follow. Concurrently, in 2005, the United Nations advocated for \"Responsible Investment by Financial Institutions,\" leading to the introduction of ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) indicators as investment guidelines. In the context of these trends in sustainable development and sustainable finance, both the public and private sectors in Taiwan—particularly corporations—face a landscape that presents both significant challenges and unique opportunities.\r\n2. The curriculum for ESG and Law (I) focuses primarily on climate change, net-zero emissions, and the law. In contrast, ESG and Law (II) shifts its focus toward the comprehensive legal framework of ESG as a whole.\r\n3. Schedule: Each instructor will conduct one session, with each session lasting four hours.\n",
